<paragraph id="905E36FFFFFCBD561F9CA8CC93760368" blockId="3.[178,1085,440,520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="464">
Comment: This species was previously known only from North 
<collectingCountry id="E8F6766FFFFCBD561CFAA8CC942D00AE" box="[980,1032,440,462]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="464">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="E8F6766FFFFCBD561F9CA8A1912A008B" box="[178,271,469,491]" name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="464">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F4704B0EFFFCBD561E33A8A1918C008B" author="ASSING V" box="[285,425,469,491]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitrage" pageId="3" pageNumber="464" pagination="221 - 244" part="43" refId="ref8323" refString="ASSING V. (2011): Orsunius gen. nov. from the Oriental region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae: Medonina). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 43 (1): 221 - 244." title="Orsunius gen. nov. from the Oriental region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae: Medonina)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="E8F6766FFFFCBD561CCEA8A29434008B" box="[992,1041,470,491]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="464">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="E8F6766FFFFCBD561F9CA886912A0368" box="[178,271,498,520]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="464">Thailand</collectingCountry>
